==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deobstruent
<hw>De*ob"stru*ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>Removing obstructions; having power to clear or open the natural
ducts of the fluids and secretions of the body; aperient.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A medicine which removes
obstructions; an aperient.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deodand</ent>⟦br⟧
